#### Dependent Territories

Dependent territories of member states are not recognized as independent members of the OECD. However, they may be included as part of their sovereign state's membership. As of January 2021, the [Dutch Caribbean](/Dutch_Caribbean) and the British territories of [Guernsey](/Guernsey), [Jersey](/Jersey), the [Isle of Man](/Isle_of_Man), [Gibraltar](/Gibraltar), and [Bermuda](/Bermuda) are incorporated into the OECD memberships of the [Netherlands](/Kingdom_of_the_Netherlands) and the [U.K.](/United_Kingdom), respectively. Other dependent territories of OECD member states do not hold OECD membership.

